AB  - Giuseppe Bertola1 Luigi Guiso2 Luigi Pistaferri3We thank David Laibson, Peter Maxted and Benjamin Moll for pointing out some incorrect statements in Section 2.1 of our paper “Uncertainty and Consumer Durables Adjustment” (The Review of Economic Studies 2005, 72, 973–1007, https://doi.org/10.1111/0034-6527.00358).On p. 982, after equation (7), the statement: “Thus, the marginal utility afforded by a higher M(t) does not depend on its within-period allocation to durables and nondurables, as indexed by the ratio Z(t) of the actual durable stock to the optimal one.” is incorrect, because X*(t) is proportional to M(t).
